<p>I have a pandas dataframe with two columns. Sequence and Acknowledgement numbers from a TCP layer. What I want to do is link each row together.i.e. the ack of row 1 = seq of row 2 and so on. This is what the function I've written looks like:</p>  <pre><code>def sortingf(data):  # Change seq and ack into strings data['seq_str'] = data['seq'].astype(str) data['ack_str'] = data['ack'].astype(str)   # Create a temporary df that will hold the sorted values temp_df=pd.DataFrame(columns=data.columns) temp_df.columns=conversation_f.columns.values data = data.sort_index(by = ['seq'], ascending=True)   for i in range(0, data.shape[0]):              # 1 DATAFRAME EMPTY     if temp_df.empty:         first_row = data.iloc[[0]]         temp_df = temp_df.append(first_row)      # DATAFRAME HAS AT LEAST ONE ROW      else:         link = temp_df.iloc[i]['ack_str']         row_link = data[data['seq_str'] == link]          # OPTION A - ACK IS IN ACK         if row_link.empty:             row_link = data[data['ack_str'] == link]             temp_df = temp_df.append(row_link)           # OPTION B - ACK IS UNIQUE -&gt; APPEND THE NEXT ROW IN ORIGINAL DATA         elif row_link.empty:             temp_df = temp_df.append(data.iloc[[i+1]])          # OPTION C: ACK IS IN SEQ -&gt; Link between conversations!         else:             temp_df=temp_df.append(row_link)   return temp_df      </code></pre>